main event: A civilian reported seeing a fast-moving object with bright navigation lights and a glowing center over Harrison, New York on August 19, 1965.
interesting points: The object was moving from north to south at a high rate of speed.
The observer could not detect any sound from the object.
The object was estimated to be about 300 yards away, 4 feet wide, and 30 feet long.
The observer had previously reported the sighting to the authorities.
The Air Force responded by sending the observer a DD Form 1396 to report the unidentified flying object.
sighted object: a fast-moving object with bright navigation lights and a glowing center
